19 Sep 2008 23:08






It seems like it would be straight-forward enough to make the maze easier to escape by, say, painting an 'OUT' sign on each door after you pass through it. Since the topology of the maze appears to be a binary tree with no intersection, this should ensure people always travel to the 'root' of the tree, i.e., the exit. At the very least, this implies that someone who follows an 'out' door should always arrive closer to the exit than they would have otherwise.

That should prevent incidents like Dr. XXXXX's disappearance, or at least make them less likely.

If this DOESN'T work, that too will be educational as to the nature of the SCP.







